    "created_at": "2017-07-11T14:15:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-07-11T14:15:25Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "`get_config()` only makes sense as part of the config file loading - it gets the config object which the rest of the file modifies.\r\n\r\nThis may be a bit tricky, unfortunately, because our config system is designed to be used with our application framework from traitlets, which I suspect ptipython doesn't use. The config needs to be loaded while the application is starting up, and passed to the IPython objects as they are instantiated.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, I don't have time at the moment to look into the ptipython code to see where it could be integrated."
